bodyText:
Summary

Removed deprecated dateSchema in favor of filterDateSchema
Replaced deprecated getDefaultClaudePath() with getClaudePaths()
Removed all deprecated functions and their test cases

Breaking Changes
This PR contains breaking changes that require users to update their code:

dateSchema removed: Use filterDateSchema instead for date validation
getDefaultClaudePath() removed: Use getClaudePaths() which returns an array of paths

Migration Guide
dateSchema â†’ filterDateSchema
// Before
import { dateSchema } from "./types";
const date = dateSchema.parse("20240101");

// After
import { filterDateSchema } from "./types";
const date = filterDateSchema.parse("20240101");
getDefaultClaudePath â†’ getClaudePaths
// Before
import { getDefaultClaudePath } from "./data-loader";
const claudePath = getDefaultClaudePath();

// After
import { getClaudePaths } from "./data-loader";
const paths = getClaudePaths();
if (paths.length === 0) {
  throw new Error("No valid Claude data directory found");
}
const claudePath = paths[0];
Test Plan

 All existing tests pass
 TypeScript compilation succeeds
 ESLint checks pass
 Verified that all deprecated function usages have been replaced
 Confirmed no references to deprecated functions remain in the codebase


Summary by CodeRabbit


Bug Fixes

Improved validation for date input fields to ensure stricter format checking.
Enhanced error handling when no valid Claude data directories are found.



Refactor

Updated logic to support multiple Claude data directories instead of relying on a single default path.
Removed deprecated date validation and legacy path selection functions for cleaner configuration.



Chores

Cleaned up unused imports and deprecated code.
